cessor, he assists Stretch in its processor direction. With a plethora of patents and publications and his deep knowledge of the semiconductor industry, Earl is a true asset to the TAB.\n |date= 2010-11-26\n |url= http://www.stretchinc.com/corporate/board.php\n |accessdate= 2010-11-26\n}}</ref><ref name=twsNovZ15>{{cite news\n |author= United States Patent Application 20060101369\n |title= Automated processor generation system for designing a configurable processor and method for the same\n |publisher= U.S. Patents Online\n |quote= ... Killian, Earl A. (Los Altos Hills, CA, US)\n |date= 2006-05-11\n |url= http://www.freepatentsonline.com/y2006/0101369.html\n |accessdate= 2010-11-26\n}}</ref>\n* [[Richard H. Kimball]], venture capitalist (graduated 1974)\n* [[William King (governor)|William King]], first [[Governor of Maine]] (graduated 1781)\n* [[Karl Kirchwey]], poet (graduated 1974)\n* [[Jonathan Philip Klein]], dog behavior consultant (graduated 1974)\n* [[William Standish Knowles]], winner of the 2001 [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry]] (graduated 1935)\n* [[Lawrence Kohlberg]], psychologist (graduated 1945)\n* [[Chris Kreider]], player for Boston College hockey team, and then New York Rangers (graduated 2010)\n* [[Erik S. Kristensen]], Lieutenant Commander, United States Navy SEALs; killed in action during Operation Red Wings (graduated 1991)<ref>http://www.lonesurvivorfilm.com/assets/img/LONESURVIVOR_productionnotes.pdf</ref>\n<!--- * [[Richard (Rick) Kimball]], [[Investment banking|investment banker]], [[Goldman Sachs]] partner,<ref>{{Cite web|title = Goldman Sachs {{!}} Press Releases - Goldman Sachs Announces New Members Of The Partnership Pool And New Managing Directors|url = http://www.goldmansachs.com/media-relations/press-releases/archived/2006/2006-10-26.html|website = www.goldmansachs.com|accessdate = 2015-10-28}}</ref> Founder of HExL.com  <ref>{{Cite web|title = HEXL: A new disruptive player in the US healthcare system|url = http://www.hedgeweek.com/2015/03/06/219589/hexl-new-disruptive-player-us-healthcare-system|website = Hedgeweek|accessdate = 2015-10-28}}</ref> (graduated 1982) not just that Kimball is not in alphabetical order here -- Wikipedia policy is that the article should be written first before the name is added to the list --->\n\n==L==\n* [[John Lardner (sports writer)|John Lardner]], sports writer\n* [[Ring Lardner, Jr.]], Academy Award-winning screenwriter\n* [[Frank Lavin]], former Undersecretary for International Trade of the U.S. Department of Commerce (graduated 1975)\n* [[George Ayres Leavitt]], early New York publisher (graduated 1840)\n* [[Gary Lee (journalist)|Gary Lee]], journalist, travel writer (graduated 1974)<ref name=twsFebL21>{{cite news\n |author= Ken Ringle\n |title= The New Yorker's Literary Lion Cub\n |newspaper= [[The Washington Post]]\n |date= August 6, 1998\n |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/style/daily/remnick.htm\n |accessdate= February 12, 2011\n}}</ref><ref name=twsFebL18>{{cite website\n |title        = Notable Alumni in the field of Journalism\n |website      = Phillips Academy\n |date         = February 12, 2011\n |url          = http://www.andover.edu/About/Newsroom/TheMagazine/Fall09/Pages/OldBlue.aspx\n |accessdate   = February 12, 2011\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20110719135209/http://www.andover.edu/About/Newsroom/TheMagazine/Fall09/Pages/OldBlue.aspx\n |archive-date = July 19, 2011\n |url-status     = dead\n}}</ref>\n*[[Nate Lee]], writer, senior editor of ''[[Newcity]]'' in Chicago (graduated 1974)<ref name=twsOctI22>{{cite web\n |title= List of Books by Nate Lee\n |website= Paperback Swap\n |date= October 31, 2010\n |url= http://www.paperbackswap.com/Nate-Lee/author/\n |accessdate= October 31, 2010\n}}</ref><ref name=twsOctI14>{{cite web\n |title= Performance Advertising: Theater, Dance, Comedy, Opera\n |website= NewCity Network\n |date= October 2009\n |url= http://newcitynetwork.com/advertising-marketing/performance-advertising-theater