out/NotableAlumni/LongList/Pages/1800s.aspx|archive-date=2013-11-05|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*[[Lisa MacFarlane]], [[List of Phillips Exeter Academy Principals|principal]] of [[Phillips Exeter Academy]] (graduated 1975)\n*[[April March]], musician and animator\n*[[Mozhan Marn\u00f2]], actress, writer, director<ref name=twsTVOM1> Aiden Mason, November 2019, TV Overmind, [https://www.tvovermind.com/mozhan-marno/ 10 Things You Didn\u2019t Know About Mozhan Marno], Retrieved January 26, 2020</ref>\n*[[George Perkins Marsh]], diplomat and philologist; credited as one of the first environmentalists (graduated 1816)\n*[[John Marsh (pioneer)|John Marsh]], early pioneer and settler in California; often regarded as the first person to practice medicine in California (graduated 1818)<ref name=Lyman>{{cite book |title=John Marsh, pioneer: The life story of a trail-blazer on six frontiers |author=George D. Lyman |publisher=Scribner's & Sons |year=1930 }}</ref>\n*[[Othniel Charles Marsh]], first professor of [[paleontology]] at [[Yale University]] (graduated 1856)\n*[[Priscilla Martel]], restaurateur and food expert (graduated 1974)<ref name=twsOctN23>{{cite news\n |author= ELIZABETH MAKER\n |title= CONNECTICUT AT ITS BEST; On an Open Fire, Much More Than Chestnuts\n |newspaper= New York Times\n |quote=  Priscilla Martel, throw in fall and winter for guests who include Morley Safer of ''60 Minutes'' and the chef Jacques P?n, both of whom live in Chester.\n |date= December 11, 2005\n |url= https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F05E0D61131F932A25751C1A9639C8B63&sec=&spon=&pagewanted=all\n |accessdate= 2010-10-20\n}}</ref>\n*[[Laurel Mass\u00e9]], founding member of [[The Manhattan Transfer]] (expelled 1969)\n*[[Barry McCaffrey|Barry R. McCaffrey]], teacher of national securities studies at [[West Point]] (graduated 1960)\n*[[Vance C. McCormick]], politician and businessman; chair of the [[American Commission to Negotiate Peace|American delegation]] at the [[Treaty of Ver