talk2014.aspx | work = [[Phillips Academy]] | title = Seth Moulton '97 talks about service on April 22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804020521/http://www.andover.edu/calendar/pages/moultontalk2014.aspx| archive-date = August 4, 2017 | url-status = dead}}</ref>\n*[[Lachlan Murdoch]], son of media mogul [[Rupert Murdoch]]; former executive director of [[News Corporation (1980\u20132013)|News Corporation]] (graduated 1990)\n*[[Charles B. G. Murphy]], writer and philanthropist; honored with the Charles B.G. Murphy professorship at Yale University (graduated 1923)\n*[[Patrick O. Murphy]], mayor of [[Lowell, Massachusetts]]\n\n==N==\n*[[Ted Nace]], computer publisher, anti-coal activist (graduated 1974)<ref name=twsNovS12>{{cite news\n |author= Monadnock Summer\n |title= Ted Nace: Confessions Of A Recovering Capitalist\n |website= New Hampshire Public Radio (NHPR)\n |date= August 8, 2004\n |url= http://www.nhpr.org/node/6718\n |accessdate= November 19, 2010\n}}</ref>{{fv|date=October 2019|reason=The cited source does not verify that Nace attended this school.}}\n*[[Joseph Hardy Neesima]], founder of [[Doshisha University]] in Japan (graduated 1867)\n*[[Sara Nelson (editor)|Sara Nelson]], former editor-in-chief of ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'' (graduated 1974)<ref name=twsOctJ25>{{cite web\n |title= Sara Nelson appears on CBS's ''The Early Show''\n |website= [[The Early Show]]\n |publisher= [[CBS News]]\n |date= December 9, 2009\n |url= http://www.cbsnews.com/video/watch/?id=5949798n\n |access-date= October 5, 2010\n |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121102184909/https://www.cbsnews.com/video/watch/?id=5949798n\n |archive-date = November 2, 2012\n |url-status = dead\n}}</ref><ref name=twsOctJ25sffwr>{{cite web\n |author= Jack Gray\n |title= Reminiscences from Reunion 1999: year (G+25), courtesy of Jack Gray.\n |website= BlueLink\n |publisher = Andover Academy\n |year= 1999\n |url= http://andoveralumni.net/classes/1974/chapterpage3.html\n |access-date=